File: Thousands of drivers have already spent time in jail for drunk driving and speeding this month. (Johannesburg Metro Police Department) JOHANNESBURG - At least 49 people have been arrested for flouting COVID-19 regulations in Johannesburg in the past 48-hours. The City's authorities are conducting major roadblocks and visiting entertainment establishments to monitor compliance. READ: COVID-19 in SA: Police enforce mask compliance "From yesterday, with Johannesburg being a hotspot, the City directed by the executive mayor took a decision that we will implement a zero-tolerance approach, especially to those who deliberately seek to undermine the regulations as stated by the President," said Johannesburg mayoral spokesperson, Mlimandlela Ndamase. Under stricter lockdown regulations, curfew begins at 9pm, and huge parties and gatherings are not allowed.